    "question_id" : 42319851,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I came up with the solution of creating a separate initialization method (not <code>setUp</code>) annotated with <code>@PostConstruct</code>. This is not really an elegant solution, but it makes sure that the autowired/injected fields are properly initialized by Spring before using them, (which was the initial problem with the statically <code>@BeforeClass</code> annotated method).</p>\n"
